On a hexagonal spiral the number at an axial coordinate \((q,r)\) is

\[
N(q,r)=1+3k(k-1)+\text{offset},
\]
where  

\(k=\max(|q|,|r|,|q+r|)\) is the ring on which the cell lies, and the offset
depends on the side of the ring.

For the neighbours of 2026 we first locate 2026 on the spiral.

---

### 1. Locate 2026  

The largest complete hex‑ring number is  

\[
M_k = 3k(k+1)+1 .
\]

\(k=26\) gives  

\[
M_{25}=3\!\times\! 25\!\times\! 26+1 = 1951 ,\qquad  
M_{26}=2107 .
\]

Hence 2026 is in ring \(k=26\).  
The first number of ring \(k\) is \(S_k=M_{k-1}+1\).

\[
S_{26}=M_{25}+1=1952 .
\]

The offset of 2026 is  

\[
\text{off}=2026-S_{26}=74 .
\]

On an axial grid the offset formula for a point on side 2 of a ring
(\(q=-k\)) is  

\[
\text{off}=3k-r .
\]

Thus the coordinate of 2026 is  

\[
(q,r)=(-26,4).
\]

---

### 2. Coordinates of the six neighbours  

Using the six axial neighbour directions  

\[
(1,0),(1,-1),(0,-1),(-1,0),(-1,1),(0,1)
\]

we obtain the neighbour coordinates

| neighbour | coordinate \((q,r)\) |
|-----------|---------------------|
| East      | \((-25,4)\) |
| NE        | \((-25,3)\) |
| NW        | \((-26,3)\) |
| West      | \((-27,4)\) |
| SW        | \((-27,5)\) |
| SE        | \((-26,5)\) |

---

### 3. Numbers of the neighbours  

For each neighbour we compute its ring \(k\), start number \(S_k\) and
offset using the same side‑2 formula \( \text{offset}=3k-r \).

| Coord | \(k\) | \(S_k\) | offset | number |
|-------|--------|----------|--------|--------|
| \((-25,4)\) | 25 | 1802 | \(3\!\times\!25-4=71\) | \(1802+71=1873\) |
| \((-25,3)\) | 25 | 1802 | \(75-3=72\) | \(1802+72=1874\) |
| \((-26,3)\) | 26 | 1952 | \(78-3=75\) | \(1952+75=2027\) |
| \((-26,5)\) | 26 | 1952 | \(78-5=73\) | \(1952+73=2025\) |
| \((-27,4)\) | 27 | 2108 | \(81-4=77\) | \(2108+77=2185\) |
| \((-27,5)\) | 27 | 2108 | \(81-5=76\) | \(2108+76=2184\) |

---

### 4. Sum of the six neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
1873 + 1874 + 2027 + 2025 + 2185 + 2184
&= 12\,168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{12\,168}
\]
